    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-25T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-25T13:00:00-05:00" n="393"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d393">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 PW/5–2546: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-25T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 25, 1946—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>974. For your <gloss target="#t_Info1">info</gloss> in connection visit Pauley to
                    northern Korea following received from Pauley today: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Please inform interested parties that Moscow’s 41,<note n="49"
                                xml:id="d393fn1">See last sentence of telegram 1609, May 22, noon,
                                from Moscow, <ref target="#pg_520">p. 520</ref>.</note> as I
                            understand it, denies my mission access as suggested in my letter of May
                            20 <pb facs="0536" n="524" xml:id="pg_524"/> to Chistiakov setting forth
                            a full itinerary and placed me in a position of either not going north
                            of the 38 parallel, or going with a bandage over my eyes.</p>
                        <p>I propose now to do the latter, but continue to press for full plan. In
                            the meantime, will establish a base at Mukden for Manchuria operation,
                            maintaining a minimum sized base in Seoul.”<note n="50" xml:id="d393fn2"
                                >In telegram 975, May 25, 4 p.m., to Moscow, the Department reported
                                Mr. Pauley’s latest message offering further limitations on his
                                proposed visit to north Korea in connection with a new request to
                                the Soviet Foreign Office (740.00119 P.W./5–2546).</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
